The paper deals with learning the preferences of a human, which is a common problem in artificial intelligence and human-computer interaction. Therefore, cs.AI and cs.HC are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also proposes a modification to uncertainty sampling, which is a common technique in machine learning and falls under cs.LG. The paper deals with natural language processing, which falls under cs.CL. Finally, the paper deals with information retrieval, which falls under cs.IR.
